{
  "stem": "12462.5",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "An appeal was made to the Control Council for Germany by all of the defendants.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[CLEARS THROAT] They each made several-- they were given, I think, two weeks, or something like this, to get them in.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the Control Council had the-- these materials translated.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they held a-- a meeting or two, and decided that they were not going to, in any way, disturb their judgment of the tribunal.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Control Council was made up of the four principal leaders of France, Great Britain, the United States, and the Soviet Union.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Control Council was a four-power group which, theoretically, had [CLEARS THROAT] some power after World War II to draw up legislation, or rules, which affected all four sections of the-- all occupation zones of Germany.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because of the Cold War coming on, the Control Council, more and more, had less power, because the-- you couldn't get cooperation between the Soviets and the Americans.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[COUGHS] But they did enact Control Council Law Number 10, which was the basis upon which we conducted the later trials, the later 12 trials.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was no-- no possibility of appealing an acquittal.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's almost impossible to, as you know, as a lawyer, to appeal an acquittal [CLEARS THROAT] of a defendant who's been discharged or found not guilty by any lower court.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, Goering is the first named defendant.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And as the first defendant that appears, as you take a picture from the back of the courtroom toward the front, Goering was clearly the most active.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He'd wave his head around and move his arms to indicate approval or disapproval of what was going on.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[CLEARS THROAT] He was the most colorful of the defendants.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
